raw_data.title: Construction Contract Auditor
raw_data.description: Responsible for coordinating detailed review of construction contracts, payment applications, change orders and labor rates. This includes interfacing with both client and contractor to discuss and review project documents. Capable of generating detailed reports that summarize project costs, identify areas that require further review, evaluate detailed labor rates, and assess fair value of change orders. The position requires experience with reading contracts and understanding how that language can play a role in project costs in terms of what is and isn’t reimbursable, allowable markups, clarifications and exclusions, allowances as part of the contract, etc. Reviewing junior team member’s work product prior to issuing to the client. Bachelor’s degree in the field of engineering, construction management, or a related field; or applicable field experience as stated in Equivalency column.
